Hi peperonigialli,

In archives, we tend to put materials into larger groupings. In this case, the heading refers to a group of images of both Matera and Molfetta, usually because that is how we found the material. We try to keep things as we found them, including descriptions that may be found on the lantern slides. If you look at the caption under the image, it will provide more specific information about the image, which in this case reads &quot;Matera; Cathedral from distance [exterior].&quot;

Angie Park, Brooklyn Museum Archives
